      "content": "but that \"empathetic system\" part sounds like a cover story for data collection. if they can track my stress levels through my lights and thermostat, they can basically build a profile of my entire mental state. wouldn't that data be incredibly valuable to advertisers or even for psychological profiling? it feels like they're running some kind of live experiment on my behavior without me knowing.",
